}}</ref> Compared to fluorescence in situ hybridization (FISH), the method uniquely allows for dynamic tracking of chromosome loci. This has been used to study chromatin architecture and nuclear organization dynamics in laboratory cell lines including HeLa cells.

===Stem cells===
Activation of [[Reprogramming|Yamanaka factors]] by CRISPRa has been used to [[Induced pluripotent stem cell|induce pluripotency]] in human and mouse cells providing an alternative method to iPS technology.<ref name=""pmid24346702"">{{Cite journal
