== In popular culture ==
In 2019, Charpentier was a featured character in the play ''STEM FEMMES'' by Philadelphia theater company Applied Mechanics.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Reinckens|first=Mina|title='STEM FEMMES' centers women in science with theater|url=https://www.broadstreetreview.com/wnwn/stem-femmes-centers-women-in-science-with-theater|access-date=24 February 2021|website=www.broadstreetreview.com}}</ref>

